Preamble
--------
FairTrack is a source-available Android calorie tracker. The source code is
published for transparency and to enable contributions. This license permits
private use and further development, but prohibits distributing copies without
clear attribution to the original project.

1. Definitions
--------------
"Software" means the source code, build scripts, resources and documentation
of this repository, as well as binaries produced from them (in particular APK
and AAB files).
"Original Project" means the rights holder's repository at
https://github.com/daonware-it/FairTrack.
"Attribution" means a clearly visible notice in the form "Based on FairTrack
(https://github.com/daonware-it/FairTrack)".

2. Permitted Use
----------------
Any person is granted, free of charge, the right to:
a) view, download, compile and use the Software for private, non-commercial
   purposes on their own devices;
b) modify the Software and use their own derivative works for private,
   non-commercial purposes;
c) submit contributions (pull requests, issues, patches) to the Original
   Project.

3. Distribution Only With Attribution
-------------------------------------
Any distribution of the Software or derivative works — in source or binary
form, whether for a fee or free of charge, including publication in app stores
— is permitted ONLY if:
a) the Attribution (Section 1) is clearly visible, at minimum in the
   description of the release AND within the app itself (e.g. in the "About"
   section);
b) this license file is included unchanged;
c) it is clearly identifiable which changes have been made relative to the
   Original Project.

4. Prohibited Acts
------------------
The following are expressly prohibited:
a) distributing the Software or derivative works WITHOUT the Attribution
